com.versant.odmg
Interface List

All Superinterfaces:
Collection
public interface List
extends Collection

A List object is an ordered collection of persistent objects. The operations defined in the List interface are positional in nature and referenced to either a given index or to the beginning or end of a List object. Indexing of a List object starts at zero.

See also the following methods in the Collection Interface:

See Also:
Collection.add(Object), Collection.contains(Object), Collection.elements(), Collection.existsElement(String), Collection.isEmpty(), Collection.query(String), Collection.remove(Object), Collection.select(String), Collection.selectElement(String), Collection.size()
